==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[minus]]-[[plus]] [[sign]]'''
#{{mathematics}} the [[symbol]] [[∓]], meaning "minus or plus", used alongside the [[plus-minus sign]] to show that a negative value is to be taken where the positive value is indicated by the plus-minus sign, and ''[[vice versa]]'' (as in (x&nbsp;±&nbsp;1)&nbsp;/&nbsp;(x&nbsp;∓&nbsp;2), which means (x&nbsp;+&nbsp;1)&nbsp;/&nbsp;(x&nbsp;-&nbsp;2) and (x&nbsp;-&nbsp;1)&nbsp;/&nbsp;(x&nbsp;+&nbsp;2)).

